    .gem-c-contents-list {
      position: -webkit-sticky;
      position: sticky;
      top: 20px;
      background: white;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__title {
      font-family: "GDS Transport", arial, sans-serif;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.25;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      color: #0b0c0c;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__list {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__list-item {
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__list-item--dashed {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash {
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: #505a5f;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash::before {
      content: "â€”";
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__link {
      font-family: "GDS Transport", arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.25;
      color: #1d70b8;
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    
    .gem-c-contents-list__link:hover {
      color: #003078;
    }
    
    /* Remove visited state to prevent purple links */
    .gem-c-contents-list__link:visited {
      color: #1d70b8;
    }
  </style>

  <!-- Page title and header -->
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="app-page-header">
        <span class="govuk-caption-xl">Delivery Group Standards</span>
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">1. Define and circulate outcomes</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body-l app-page-header__summary">
          Clear outcomes that everyone understands and works towards.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third app-sticky-element">
      <!-- Page contents -->
      <nav class="gem-c-contents-list govuk-!-margin-bottom-8" aria-label="Contents">
        <h2 class="gem-c-contents-list__title">Contents</h2>
        <ol class="gem-c-contents-list__list">
          <li class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item gem-c-contents-list__list-item--dashed">
            <span class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <a class="gem-c-contents-list__link govuk-link" href="#why-its-important">Why it's important</a>
          </li>
          <li class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item gem-c-contents-list__list-item--dashed">
            <span class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <a class="gem-c-contents-list__link govuk-link" href="#what-you-should-show">What you should be able to show</a>
          </li>
          <li class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item gem-c-contents-list__list-item--dashed">
            <span class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <a class="gem-c-contents-list__link govuk-link" href="#how-it-is-measured">How it is measured</a>
          </li>
          <li class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item gem-c-contents-list__list-item--dashed">
            <span class="gem-c-contents-list__list-item-dash" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <a class="gem-c-contents-list__link govuk-link" href="#delivery-group-standards">Delivery group standards</a>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="why-its-important">Why it's important</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        When delivery groups have clear, well-communicated outcomes, teams stay focused on what 
        matters most. Everyone pulls in the same direction, making decisions that advance shared 
        goals rather than working at cross-purposes. This alignment accelerates delivery and 
        ensures effort translates into meaningful impact.
      </p>

      <p class="govuk-body">
        Without clear outcomes, teams waste time on activities that don't contribute to success, 
        stakeholders lose confidence, and it becomes impossible to demonstrate value or learn 
        from what works.
      </p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="what-you-should-show">What you should be able to show</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        To demonstrate that your delivery group meets this standard, you should be able to:
      </p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>Define and document 3-5 clear, specific outcomes that align to departmental priorities</li>
        <li>Show that all team members can consistently describe the outcomes in the same way</li>
        <li>Provide evidence of regular communication about outcomes to stakeholders</li>
        <li>Demonstrate clear ownership and accountability for delivering each outcome</li>
        <li>Present a team charter or mission statement that clearly articulates your outcomes</li>
        <li>Show how decisions are made with reference to these outcomes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="how-it-is-measured">How it is measured</h2>
      
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Each standard is measured using a RAG (Red, Amber, Green) rating system.
      </p>

      <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          {{ govukTag({
            text: "Green",
            classes: "govuk-tag--green govuk-!-margin-right-2"
          }) }}
          Clear, well-documented outcomes aligned to strategic goals
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Delivery group has clearly defined, documented outcomes that are well understood 
          by all team members and consistently communicated. Outcomes are explicitly 
          aligned to departmental or strategic objectives.
        </p>
        <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Evidence you might provide:</h4>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Outcome framework document showing clear alignment to departmental strategy</li>
          <li>Team charter or mission statement with defined outcomes</li>
          <li>Stakeholder communications clearly articulating outcomes</li>
          <li>Evidence that all team members can consistently describe the outcomes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          {{ govukTag({
            text: "Amber",
            classes: "govuk-tag--yellow govuk-!-margin-right-2"
          }) }}
          Outcomes documented but not consistently understood or communicated
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Outcomes exist but may be vague, inconsistently understood across the team, 
          or not regularly communicated to stakeholders. Alignment to departmental 
          objectives may be unclear or incomplete.
        </p>
        <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Common issues:</h4>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>Outcomes are too high-level or aspirational without specificity</li>
          <li>Different team members give different descriptions of outcomes</li>
          <li>Limited evidence of alignment to departmental priorities</li>
          <li>Infrequent or inconsistent communication to stakeholders</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
          {{ govukTag({
            text: "Red",
            classes: "govuk-tag--red govuk-!-margin-right-2"
          }) }}
          Unclear or missing outcomes
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Outcomes are vague, undocumented, or inconsistent across the group. 
          No clear understanding of what success looks like or how it connects 
          to departmental objectives.
        </p>
        <h4 class="govuk-heading-s">Indicators of this rating:</h4>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li>No documented outcomes or only high-level aspirations</li>
          <li>Team members cannot clearly articulate what they're trying to achieve</li>
          <li>No clear connection to departmental or strategic objectives</li>
          <li>Focus is on activities rather than outcomes</li>
          <li>Stakeholders have different understanding of what the group is delivering</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="delivery-group-standards">Delivery group standards</h2>
      <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
        <li><strong>Define and circulate outcomes</strong></li>
        <li><a href="/delivery-group-standards/2" class="govuk-link">Maintain an inventory of products and services</a></li>
        <li><a href="/delivery-group-standards/3" class="govuk-link">Publish a plan for change</a></li>
        <li><a href="/delivery-group-standards/4" class="govuk-link">Define success measures and share progress</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}